---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Brandmark from '../components/Brandmark.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Nota">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pb-20 pt-14">
    <span class="chip font-mono">
      <Brandmark size={14} />
      A note from the maker
    </span>

    <h1 class="mt-5 h-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl">
      Nota started with a kopi receipt.
    </h1>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 font-display text-lg leading-[1.7] text-ink-700">
      <p>
        I scanned my GoFood receipts at the end of one week and realised I had
        spent almost a million rupiah on coffee. Not on dinners, not on
        groceries, not on anything memorable — coffee. I had no idea.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every personal-finance app expects you to type. Every receipt scanner I
        tried wanted an account, a subscription, a referral code. Nobody just
        looked at the paper, told me what I bought, and stopped there.
      </p>
      <p>
        Nota is the small, honest version of that — drop a struk, get one warm
        Bahasa Indonesia sentence, see the week add up.
      </p>
      <p>
        Under the hood, three of Xiaomi's MiMo models do all the work: a vision
        model reads the receipt, a reasoning model categorises it and writes
        the insight, and a TTS model reads you a 60-second weekly recap on
        Sunday. None of your data leaves the tab.
      </p>
      <p class="text-ink-300">
        <em>Built for the Xiaomi MiMo Orbit creator program, May 2026.</em>
      </p>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-12 border-ink-100" />

    <div class="grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="pop p-5">
        <div class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-ink-800">For users</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-500">
          Nota will never sell anything to you. There is no upsell, no
          marketplace integration, no "premium" plan. It's a tool, not a funnel.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pop p-5">
        <div class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-ink-800">For the MiMo reviewer</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-500">
          The full pipeline source is in <code class="rounded bg-bone-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">src/lib/server/pipeline.ts</code>.
          Per-scan token usage is shown on every receipt card. The architecture
          page has a code preview of the live MiMo SDK calls.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 text-center">
      <a
        href="/scan"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-md bg-ink-800 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-bone-50 transition hover:bg-ink-700"
      >
        Try the scanner →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
